      "file_path": "bpmn/so-bpmn-tasks/src/main/java/org/onap/so/bpmn/infrastructure/service/level/impl/ServiceLevelPrepareImpl.java",
      "patchset_number": 12,
      "line": 86,
      "message": "As we are invoking exceptionBuilder rather than throwing exception directly, compiler will force to return something outside switch block, even after throwing exception in default case. But logically that would be an unreachable code. To avoid this we have to introduce local variable like before and return it at the end of the method. Can i follow the old approach again?\n\n        String wflName = null;\n        switch(scope.toLowerCase()){\n            case \"pnf\":\n                wflName =  GENERIC_PNF_HEALTH_CHECK_WORKFLOW;\n                break;\n            case \"vnf\":\n                wflName =  GENERIC_VNF_HEALTH_CHECK_WORKFLOW;\n                break;\n            default:\n                exceptionBuilder.buildAndThrowWorkflowException(execution, ERROR_CODE,\n                        \"No valid health check work flow retrieved for the scope: \" + scope);\n        }\n        return wflName;",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 6070,
        "name": "Ramesh Murugan Iyer",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "ramesh.murugan.iyer@est.tech",
        "username": "rameshiyer27"
      },
      "updated": "2020-08-04 17:00:01.000000000",
